{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Psychic}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Psychic|prevnum=676|prev=Furfrou|nextnum=678|next=Meowstic}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Espurr\n|jname=ニャスパー\n|jtranslit=Nyasupā\n|tmname=Nyasper\n|category=Restraint\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Psychic\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Keen Eye\n|ability2=Infiltrator\n|abilityd=Own Tempo\n|ndex=677\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=114\n|height-ftin=1\'00"\n|height-m=0.3\n|weight-lbs=7.7\n|weight-kg=3.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evsp=1\n|expyield=71\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|color=Gray\n|catchrate=190\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=espurr\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Espurr\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ニャスパー\'\'\' \'\'Nyasper\'\') is a {{type|Psychic}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Meowstic}} starting at level 25.\n\n==Biology==\nEspurr is a bipedal, feline Pokémon. Its fur is a pale gray with white tips on its ears and white paws. There are tousled tufts of fur on its head, cheeks, shoulders, chest, and hips. It has wide, pale purple eyes with darker purple pupils, a tiny nose, and a small mouth. When its mouth is open, two pointed teeth can be seen on its upper jaw. Its tail is fluffy and slightly curled.\n\nEspurr\'s ears are quite large in proportion to its body and folded. Beneath its ears are two ring-shaped yellow organs. These organs emit Espurr\'s intense psychic powers. It has no control over its power, and it would leak out if the ears were not sheltering the organs. It has enough psychic energy to create a blast radius of 300 feet (90 meters).\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Elise Espurr.png|thumb|250px|left|Espurr in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\nEspurr debuted in \'\'[[XY014|Seeking Shelter from the Storm!]]\'\', where it was the sole resident of an abandoned mansion belonging to its deceased owner {{OBP|Lacy|XY014}}.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY039|Summer of Discovery!]]\'\' and \'\'[[XY041|Foggy Pokémon Orienteering!]]\'\', and in a picture in \'\'[[XY042|Battling Into the Hall of Fame!]]\'\'. It was one of the Pokémon that participated in the [[Pokémon Summer Camp]].\n\nAn Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY040|Day Three Blockbusters!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Espurr appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[XY045|Splitting Heirs!]]\'\', under the ownership of two brothers, {{OBP|Blake|XY045}} and {{OBP|Heath|XY045}}.\n\nAn Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY062|The Future Is Now, Thanks to Determination!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY091|A Performance Pop Quiz!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY092|Cloudy Fate, Bright Future!]]\'\'. One was under the ownership of a {{tc|Psychic}}, while the other was owned by a Trainer.\n\nAn Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY105|Party Dancecapades!]]\'\', under the ownership of a [[Pokémon Performer]] participating in [[Monsieur Pierre]]\'s dance party.\n\nThree Espurr appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as residents of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY138|The First Day of the Rest of Your Life!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer with three Espurr appeared in \'\'[[XY129|Kalos League Passion with a Certain Flare!]]\'\'.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY014|Espurr|Ash\'s Pokédex|Espurr, the Restraint Pokémon. Espurr\'s {{t|Psychic}} energy can travel hundreds of feet, blasting everything around it.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Mimi PG.png|thumb|250px|Espurr in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\n[[Emma]]\'s Espurr, [[nickname]]d [[Emma#Pokémon|Mimi]], appeared in \'\'[[PG17|The Investigation]]\'\'. It accompanied [[Looker]] on a search of [[Lumiose City]] as he was searching for Essentia. Mimi\'s affection towards Essentia provided the proof for Looker that she was Emma in disguise, and Mimi later led him towards her.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Emma Mimi Adventures.png|thumb|130px|Espurr in the [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nEspurr debuted in \'\'[[PAXY05|Kangaskhan...Kangascan\'t]]\'\', where it appeared by the fountain in [[Santalune City]] with its {{pkmn|Trainer}}.\n\nA {{tc|Team Flare Grunt}} used four Espurr with different expressions to stall {{adv|Y}}, {{adv|Tierno}}, and {{adv|Shauna}} in \'\'[[PAXY13|Overthrowing a Tyrunt]]\'\'. Cassius arrived and helped the three with his {{p|Gourgeist}}, {{pkmn2|caught|catching}} three of them. Later, [[Emma]] found the last Espurr, who had gotten {{status|confusion|confused}}, and [[nickname]]d it Mimi.\n\nAn Espurr appeared in \'\'[[PAXY33|Chesnaught Protects]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Pokémon Village]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Espurr (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* {{g|X and Y}}: [[Emma]]\'s closest friend is an Espurr she named Mimi (Japanese: \'\'\'もこお\'\'\' \'\'Mokō\'\'). It helps Emma, [[Looker]], and the {{player}} several times during the Looker Bureau sidequest.\n* {{g|Super Mystery Dungeon}}: Espurr is one of the {{mdc|students|smd}} who live in [[Serene Village]]. She is clever and reliable. She uses her telepathy to good use during the game, helping to distract {{p|Watchog}} and keep in touch with {{p|Ampharos}}.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=psychic}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=114|label1=Central|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within {{tt|300 feet|90 meters}} of itself, but it has no control over its power.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep 